class Solution {
public:
    int flipLights(int n, int presses) {
        if (presses == 0) return 1;
        if (n == 1) return 2;
        if (n == 2) return presses == 1 ? 3 : 4;
        return presses == 1 ? 4 : (presses == 2 ? 7 : 8);
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution directly returns the number of different possible statuses based on the given n and presses, leveraging the fact that the number of possible statuses is limited and can be precomputed for different cases of n and presses.
